In article <C8D7qy.JIH@acsu.buffalo.edu> boyd@acsu.buffalo.edu (Daniel F Boyd) writes:
> Who invented RSA?  Professionals.  DES?  Professionals.  FEAL, IDEA,
> Snefru, Khufu?  Professionals.

It was academics, IBM, the Japanese, the Swiss, and Xerox respectively.

In the last 15 years non-governmental cryptography has moved forward at 
amazing speed. I see no evidence, beyond Bobby Inman's assertions, that 
the NSA has kept ahead.

